data.title: The Femení, in the podium of the Champions and the FC Barcelona already brushes the 50 Glasses of Europe like club
data.meta_description: The FC Barcelona Femení has won his third Champions League, the second consecutive, to close a historical season, with triplete, and leave the name of the Barcelona picture even more high
data.text:
The FC Barcelona Femení has completed a historical season, in all the senses. They have topped it with the Champions League, after his victory in front of the Olympique of Lyon (2-0) in which Aitana Bonmatí and Alexia Putellas dressed of stars to lead a magic afternoon in Saint Mamés. They were many the difficulties in front of his 'black beast' in Europe, put had fallen in the four parties that had contested in front of the Lyon, included two finals.

Already they are three Champions League for the Barcelona picture and the second consecutive. It has served them to complete the second triplete of titles of his history, remembering that they already had won before the League F and Glass of Rey. To this, it is necessary to add him the Supercopa of Spain. A 'póker' that confirms the state of grace of the Barcelona, that follow showing that they are the best team of the world in the actuality.

For the FC Barcelona is a big joy, especially in a year that has been marked by the disappointments of the masculine group. With the Champions achieved in Saint Mamés, already are 47 glasses that adds the club between all his sections in Europe. They can add a more and remain to 'swim' of the 50, remembering that the team of handball will play the second semifinal of the Final Four of the Champions. It will be in front of the Kiel and, in case to win, will measure to the Magdeburgo on 9 June.

The 47 Glasses in Europe of the FC Barcelona

Hockey on skate (22): 1972-73, 1973-74, 1977-78, 1978-79, 1979-80, 1980-81, 1981-82, 1982-83, 1983-84, 1984-85, 1996-97, 1999-00, 2000-01, 2001-02, 2003-04, 2004-05, 2006-07, 2007-08, 2009-10, 2013-14, 2014-15, 2017-18.

Handball (11): 1990-91, 1995-96, 1996-97, 1997-98, 1998-99, 1999-00, 2004-05, 2010-11, 2014-15, 2020-21, 2021-22.

Masculine football (5): 1991-92, 2005-06, 2008-09, 2010-11, 2014-15.

Five-a-side football (5): 2011-12, 2013-14, 2019-20, 2021-22, 2023-24.

Feminine football (3): 2020-21, 2022-23, 2023-24.

Basket (2): 2002-03, 2009-10.

The Barça Femení, in the podium

On the other hand, with the victory in front of the Olympique of Lyon, the Barça Femení has 'colado' definitively in the podium of the clubs with more titles in the Champions League feminine, only by behind his rival in this final, that adds eight trophies, and the Frankfurt, that has won four. With two crowns, find the Umea, Wolfsburgo and Turbine Potsdam. The teams that have a trophy are Arsenal and Duisburgo.
